title: How has the number of ambulance staff changed over time?
analysis_commentary: There is annual variation in the number of ambulance staff with a trough each summer followed by a rise as newly qualified staff join the workforce, reaching a peak in the winter. There has been an increase in the number of ambulance staff over the past five years, from 17,234 in September 2009 to 17,802 in May 2015.
data_source: Health & Social Care Information Centre, NHS Hospital & Community Health Service Workforce Statistics
